frus:attachment.p:
George Harwood, boatswain’s mate; English pensioner; from English navy;
                            joined her at Liverpool home; now is a southerner, as boatswain; lives
                            in Liverpool.

Joseph Conner, seaman, Englishman; resides in Walnut street. His wife
                            lives there and keeps a butcher’s shop; belongs to naval reserve;
                            enlisted at Terceira.
